SIMPLE: lockage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lockage
<hw>Lock"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Materials
for locks in a canal, or the works forming a lock or locks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Toll paid for passing the locks of a
canal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Amount of elevation and descent made by the locks of
a canal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The entire <qex>lock</qex> will be about fifty feet.</q>
<rj><qau>De Witt Clinton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lockbox</ent>⟦br⟧
